{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Replace the e-petitions system with a People's PMQs",
        "additional_details": "A rough outline would be a bi-monthly period for the PM (and possibly other cabinet members) to answer questions that were submitted and voted on by the public (in a similar style to petitions now). These would be independently vetted and approved.",
        "background": "We believe that neither the current PMQs or petition system provide effective scrutiny of Government or voice to the public, and that a new People\u2019s PMQs should be established to allow questions submitted and voted on by the public to be asked of the Prime Minister.",
